<span class="header1">FINANCE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field are for people who are able to investigate and are good at numbers. If you would like to work with finances, these occupations might be for you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Accountant</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/1287.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Accountant" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy working with numbers, you might become an accountant. An accountant is responsible for helping a company make money. You might advise the company to buy or sell stock, or you might prepare its taxes.  You would also keep careful records so that it was possible to tell how much money the company made and where this money was spent.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree for an entry level job. Most accountants are CPA's (Certified Public Accountants). To become a CPA, you must have a Bachelor's Degree. You must also pass a written exam.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A CPA makes $30,000 to $82,000+ per year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Statistician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/C1618_03.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Statistician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a statistician, you would gather information in numbers. For example, Major League Baseball players have their batting averages determined by statisticians. If you worked in a business, you would look at certain numbers to see how well the company was doing.  Is it in good shape? Numbers give the statistician the answer.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree in statistics or mathematics for this job.  To get a promotion, you must have a Master's Degree or a Ph.D.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average salary for a statistician is $57,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Loan Officer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/C506008.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Loan Officer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A loan officer works for a bank or lending company. As a loan officer, you would help customers fill out loan applications and make sure that the information on the application is correct. You would then see if the people wanting the loan met your company's guidelines for a loan. If so, you would help to process the loan.  If not, you would help them to understand why they did not get the loan.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  Some banks and lending companies only hire those with a Master's Degree in business administration.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary range for a loan officer is $25,000 to $88,000 per year.</blockquote>

