<span class="header1">MEDICAL</span>
<p>Health care is one area where business and science blend well. The occupations in this field need people who are interested in the physical well-being of others.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Public Health Administrator</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/C506006.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Public Health Administrator" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Because many illnesses can be passed to others, it is important to have people who help to guard against widespread illnesses. This person is a public health administrator. In this job, you would oversee the health care programs of a county or city.  You would make sure that the hospitals, clinics, and health departments follow the rules set by the state or local government.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>All people who work as health care administrators must have a Master's Degree. Some health care administrators have degrees in public health. Others have a degree in public administration.  Still others have a degree in business administration.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $37,000 to $100,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Nursing Home Director</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a nursing home director, you would make sure that the building and equipment are kept in good condition.  You would also make sure that the elderly people who live in the home are well cared for. An important part of your duties would be to oversee the employees who care for the elderly. Another important duty is to run the home so that it earns a profit.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>All people who work as health care administrators must have a Master's Degree. Some health care administrators have degrees in public health.  Others have a degree in public administration.  Still others have a degree in business administration.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary ranges from $55,000 to $100,000+.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Patient Representative</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like to make sure others are treated well, you might become a patient representative. In this job, you would act as a go-between for the hospital and its employees and patients. For example, if a patient felt he/she was being treated poorly or unfairly, you would step in to help. You would talk with employees and the patient.  Then you would work out the best plan for getting appropriate care for the patient.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a high school diploma for this job. More and more people with Bachelor's Degrees are going into this occupation.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary ranges from $15,000 to $51,000.</blockquote>

