<span class="header1">ANALYSIS/RESEARCH</span>
<p>In this field, employees need to understand how to make money and how to do business. If you chose to work in this field, you would study how business is practiced and what companies must do to make money.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Economist</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy finding clues and drawing conclusions, you might become an economist. An economist looks at trends in business and predicts what will happen. For example, you might study the oil business and decide whether the price of gasoline will be going up or down. You would probably like this job if you are naturally curious and enjoy a challenge.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Master's Degree for this job. Many employers will want you to have a Ph.D. Education is very important.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The salary ranges from $40,000 to $128,000 a year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Market Researcher</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/43326.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Market Researcher" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A market researcher works for a company that makes a product sold to the public. As a researcher, you might work for a toy manufacturer or a retail store. You would collect information about what customers want to buy and give your results to the company.  If you are curious and understand business, this might be a good job for you.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  Market researchers start out in entry-level jobs, then they are promoted to this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $29,000 to $100,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Computer Systems Analyst</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/43166.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Computer Systems Analyst" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Businesses are always looking for a new way to make their offices run smoothly. A computer systems analyst looks for ways to make the day-to-day tasks of a business easier. You would make suggestions on which computer systems would be best for the company. You would also help the company come up with new ways to route information.  To be a good computer systems analyst, you must know a lot about computers and be able to work with different types of people.  People who do this job are also called computer engineers.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a high school diploma for this job. It is also helpful to have taken courses in computer science, technology and programming.  Experience with computers will help you to get a job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $39,000 to $93,000.</blockquote>

